# Ekya — Build Walkthrough

## What Was Built

Ekya is an E2EE Real-Time Collaborative CRDT Framework — a developer SDK where the central server **never sees plaintext data**. The complete framework was built from scratch in a single session.

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["EkyaDocument<br/>(Developer API)"] --> B["CRDT Engine<br/>GCounter | LWWRegister | LWWMap | RGA"]
    B --> C["Serializer<br/>(MessagePack)"]
    C --> D["EncryptedEnvelope<br/>(AES-256-GCM)"]
    D --> E["SyncProtocol<br/>(Dedup + Epoch)"]
    E --> F["WebSocketTransport<br/>(Reconnection)"]
    F --> G["Trustless Relay Server<br/>(Blind Forwarding)"]
    
    H["KeyManager<br/>(ECDH P-256 + HKDF)"] --> D
    I["KeyRotation<br/>(Epoch-based)"] --> D
    J["AwarenessProtocol<br/>(Cursors/Presence)"] --> F
    K["EkyaProvider<br/>(Orchestrator)"] --> A
    K --> E
    K --> J
```

