## Critical Bug Fix: RGA Convergence

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Found and fixed a convergence bug during testing — exactly the kind of "brutal to debug" issue warned about in the review.

**Problem**: [elemIdEquals(null, null)](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/core/RGA.js#65-76) returned `false` because the original implementation used `a && b && ...` which short-circuits on `null`. When two peers both insert at position 0 (afterId=null), the sibling ordering scan was never executed.

**Impact**: Concurrent inserts at the start of a document would produce different orderings on different peers — a fundamental CRDT correctness violation.

**Fix**: Explicit null equality check before the object property comparison:

```diff
 static elemIdEquals(a, b) {
-    return a && b && a.nodeId === b.nodeId && a.seq === b.seq;
+    if (a === null && b === null) return true;
+    if (a === null || b === null) return false;
+    return a.nodeId === b.nodeId && a.seq === b.seq;
 }
```

